# Release information

* introduce and test interesting features
* run the style and syntax check: make check
* increase VERSION in bdsync_manager/__init__.py
* update the changelog
* create a release announcement (website/content/release-X.Y.md)
* commit the above release information changes
* set a release tag: git tag -a vX.Y [COMMIT_ID]
* create a signed release archive: make sign
* upload to savannah: make upload UPLOAD_USER=savannah_username
* upload to pypi: make pypi-upload
* add release announcement to website: make website-upload
* add a release announcement to the savannah project website
* send a release announcement to the mailing list
* add and commit the release archive (and the signature)
* push all changes
